was first opened in 1990 in the downtown
area of our city. But we moved to this new
building last year. We have over 40,000
historic items, and about 10,000 books about
paper. They will help you know a lot about
paper. We also offer a special program where
you can have a chance to make traditional
paper on your own. It will cost you 5 dollars.
On your way out, you can buy various items
made of paper at the souvenir shop. Enjoy
your visit to our museum. Thanks!
